  "time_ut": 1657537723,
  "original_lang": "ta",
  "original_title": "\u0bae\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0baf \u0b85\u0bb1\u0bbf\u0bb5\u0bbf\u0baa\u0bcd\u0baa\u0bc8 \u0bb5\u0bc6\u0bb3\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bb0\u0ba3\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Ranil made the important announcement",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe stated that he accepted the post of Prime Minister because of the economic crisis and pointed out that it will take four years to stabilize the economy and the International Monetary Fund has mentioned that the first year is the worst.",
        "He mentioned the above in a special video released by him today (11).",
        "The Prime Minister said that after the protest on the 9th, the protesters who were going home were told by the police to leave the house as there might be unrest when they passed by his house and after that he and his wife left the house.",
        "He mentioned that the only house he had in the country and abroad was burnt down today and the most destroyed property was his books which included limited edition and rare books.",
        "He said that he and his wife had decided to gift 2500 books from the Portuguese period and Dutch period books to Peradeniya University, Royal College and many other places.",
        "He mentioned that there were more ancient pictures than that, and there was a 200-year-old Dutch picture of King Vimaladharmasuriya meeting the Dutch ambassador and there was only one picture left.",
        "He pointed out that these two weeks are important for the International Monetary Fund discussions and are necessary for fuel and food procurement.",
        "He said that the government should be law-abiding and act according to the provisions of the constitution and that it is the prime minister who is responsible for protecting the constitution and listening to the grievances of the people.",
        "MP Raoob Hakeem had tweeted that evening that the Prime Minister did not agree with the party leaders' meeting on Saturday (09) and in response to MA Sumanthran MP's question as to why the Prime Minister did not want to resign, he resigned after forming a new government. He said he was ready."
      ],
